entry.summary:
Recently, several bounds have been obtained on the number of solutions to congruences of the type $$ (x_1+s)...(x_{
u}+s)\equiv (y_1+s)...(y_{
u}+s)
ot\equiv0 \pmod p $$ modulo a prime $p$ with variables from some short intervals. Here, for almost all $p$ and all $s$ and also for a fixed $p$ and almost all $s$, we derive stronger bounds. We also use similar ideas to show that for almost all primes, one can always find an element of a large order in any rather short interval.
